		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Phosphene</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For the band or album called Seeing Stars, see <a href="/wiki/Seeing_Stars_(band/album)" title="Seeing Stars (band/album)">Seeing Stars (band/album)</a>.</div>
<dl>
<dd><i>"Phosphene" is also a common alternative spelling of <a href="/wiki/Phosphine" title="Phosphine">Phosphine</a>, PH<sub>3</sub>, a toxic and explosive gas.</i></dd>
</dl>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:402px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Phosphene_artistic_depiction.gif" class="image" title="Artistic representation of a phosphene, caused by mechanical stimulation of the retina."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2a/Phosphene_artistic_depiction.gif" width="400" height="217" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Phosphene_artistic_depiction.gif" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Artistic representation of a phosphene, caused by mechanical stimulation of the <a href="/wiki/Retina" title="Retina">retina</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A <b>phosphene</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Entoptic_phenomenon" title="Entoptic phenomenon">entoptic phenomenon</a> characterized by the experience of seeing <a href="/wiki/Light" title="Light">light</a> without light actually entering the <a href="/wiki/Eye" title="Eye">eye</a>. The word <i>phosphene</i> comes from the Greek words <i>phos</i> (light) and <i>phainein</i> (to show).<sup id="cite_ref-carr_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-carr-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Phosphenes can be directly induced by mechanical, electrical, or magnetic stimulation of the <a href="/wiki/Retina" title="Retina">retina</a> or <a href="/wiki/Visual_cortex" title="Visual cortex">visual cortex</a> as well as by random firing of cells in the <a href="/wiki/Visual_system" title="Visual system">visual system</a>. Phosphenes have also been reported by <a href="/wiki/Meditation" title="Meditation">meditators</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> people who go for long periods without visual stimulation (also known as the <a href="/wiki/Prisoner%27s_cinema" title="Prisoner's cinema">prisoner's cinema</a>) or who are under the influence of drugs, especially a <a href="/wiki/Hallucinogenic_drugs" title="Hallucinogenic drugs" class="mw-redirect">hallucinogen</a>.</p>
