<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://jp.physoc.org/cgi/reprint/196/2/479.pdf" class="external text" title="http://jp.physoc.org/cgi/reprint/196/2/479.pdf" rel="nofollow">"The sensations produced by electrical stimulation of the visual cortex"</a> (PDF). The Journal of Physiology Online<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://jp.physoc.org/cgi/reprint/196/2/479.pdf" class="external free" title="http://jp.physoc.org/cgi/reprint/196/2/479.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://jp.physoc.org/cgi/reprint/196/2/479.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+sensations+produced+by+electrical+stimulation+of+the+visual+cortex&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=The+Journal+of+Physiology+Online&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fjp.physoc.org%2Fcgi%2Freprint%2F196%2F2%2F479.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Phosphene"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://jn.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/93/1/1.pdf" class="external text" title="http://jn.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/93/1/1.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Phosphene Induction and the Generation of Saccadic Eye Movements by Striate Cortex"</a> (PDF). Journal of Neurophysiology<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://jn.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/93/1/1.pdf" class="external free" title="http://jn.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/93/1/1.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://jn.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/93/1/1.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Phosphene+Induction+and+the+Generation+of+Saccadic+Eye+Movements+by+Striate+Cortex&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Journal+of+Neurophysiology&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fjn.physiology.org%2Fcgi%2Freprint%2F93%2F1%2F1.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Phosphene"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFFugelsangNarici_L.2C_Picozza_P.2C_Sannita_WG2006">Fugelsang, C; Narici L, Picozza P, Sannita WG (April 2006). "<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&amp;uid=16676658&amp;cmd=showdetailview" class="external text" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&amp;uid=16676658&amp;cmd=showdetailview" rel="nofollow">Phosphenes in low earth orbit: survey responses from 59 astronauts</a>". <i>Aviation, space, and environmental medicine</i> <b>77</b> (4): 449–452. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16676658" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16676658">PMID 16676658</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&amp;uid=16676658&amp;cmd=showdetailview" class="external free" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&amp;uid=16676658&amp;cmd=showdetailview" rel="nofollow">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&amp;uid=16676658&amp;cmd=showdetailview</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-27</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Phosphenes+in+low+earth+orbit%3A+survey+responses+from+59+astronauts&amp;rft.jtitle=Aviation%2C+space%2C+and+environmental+medicine&amp;rft.aulast=Fugelsang&amp;rft.aufirst=C&amp;rft.au=Fugelsang%2C+C&amp;rft.au=Narici+L%2C+Picozza+P%2C+Sannita+WG&amp;rft.date=April+2006&amp;rft.volume=77&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=449%E2%80%93452&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/16676658&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fsites%2Fentrez%3Fdb%3Dpubmed%26uid%3D16676658%26cmd%3Dshowdetailview&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Phosphene"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> Grüsser, O. J., Grüsser-Cornehls, U., Hagner, M., &amp; Przybyszewski, A. W. (1989). Purkyne's description of pressure phosphenes and modern neurophysiological studies on the generation of phosphenes by eyeball deformation. Physiologia bohemoslovaca, 38(289-309), 1059-1068.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> Gruesser O-J, Hagner M. On the history of deformation phosphenes and the idea of internal light generated in the eye for the purpose of vision. <i>Documenta Ophthalmologica</i> 74 (1990): 57-85.</li>
</ol>
</div>
